      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Relying on high doses of garlic and leafy greens to replace warfarin is extremely dangerous and could put you at high risk for dangerous blood clots. Garlic has natural blood-thinning properties, which means taking too much could cause excessive bleeding when combined with other factors. Your doctor prescribes warfarin to maintain a specific, safe balance; attempting to self-adjust with supplements is not safe and can have severe medical consequences. Please communicate your concerns about lab testing to your physician to find a mutually agreeable management plan.",
      "source": "target",
